The file (SHA256:f014123c33b362df3549010ac8b37d7b28e002fc9264c54509ac8834b66e15ad) has a low VT score: 4/61, even if not obfuscated. This prooves that a simple concatenation of files helps to deliver malicious code. The payload can be easily extracted via a few lines of Python:with open("malicious.png", "rb") as f:
